esolved","sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"From version 43.0.0 the implementation points to rust_openssl, where there is a check performed while decrypting the max length of cipher shouldn't exceed 2^{16} .\r\n\r\nI referred the implementation of decrypt using AESCCM here https://github.com/pyca/cryptography/blob/43.0.3/src/rust/src/backend/aead.rs\r\n\r\nOn decryption the validation is including the appended tag bytes in the length that is validated. This results in an error while decrypting valid ciphertext.\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\nwith a 13 byte Nonce and the maximum payload size of 65535 bytes, the decryption operation would fail.\r\n\r\nfrom cryptography.hazmat.primitives.ciphers.aead import AESCCM\r\n\r\naes_ccm_max_length_plaintext = b\"A\" * 65535\r\naad = b\"authenticated but unencrypted data\"\r\nkey = AESCCM.generate_key(bit_length=256)\r\naesccm = AESCCM(key)\r\nnonce = os.urandom(13)\r\n\r\nencrypted_plaintext = aesccm.encrypt(nonce, aes_ccm_max_length_plaintext, aad)\r\ndecrypted_data = aesccm.decrypt(nonce, ct, aad)\r\n\r\n> Value Error: Data too long for nonce\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"reaperhulk","id":161495,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE2MTQ5NQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/161495?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/reaperhulk","html_url":"https://github.com/reaperhulk","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/reaperhulk/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/reaperhulk/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/reaperhulk/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/reaperhulk/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/reaperhulk/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/reaperhulk/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/reaperhulk/repos","events